Given I'm logged-in with valid credentials
When I select 'Female' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select 'MRI pelvic floor' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
Then I go to Page 03 and select 'Yes' in Contrast enhanced
Then I select 'Sequences' box
And select 'Oral contrast' checkbox
Then I go to Page 08 of Pelvic MRI
And I click on 'Finding' radio button
And dropdown below 'Finding' is enabled

When I select 'Appendicitis' from the dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Characterization I' tab is preselected

When I select 'Characterization II' tab
Then 'Strong' radio button is enabled
And 'Low' radio button is enabled
And 'No' radio button is enabled

And '„Target-sign“' checkbox is enabled
And 'CM Enhancement in the environment' checkbox is enabled

And 'Ulcerating/phlegmonous infiltration' radio button is enabled
And 'Gangrenous' radio button is enabled
And 'Perforated' radio button is enabled

And 'Differential diagnosis' dropdown is enabled

When I select 'Strong' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Heterogeneous' radio button
Then 'Central' radio button is enabled
And 'Peripheral' radio button is enabled
And 'Mural' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Low' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Heterogeneous' radio button
Then 'Central' radio button is enabled
And 'Peripheral' radio button is enabled
And 'Mural' radio button is enabled

When I select any option from the 'Differential diagnosis' dropdown
Then 'Subordinate' checkbox is enabled
